In regard to the concepts pertaining to evaluation (&#x201C;value,&#x201D; &#x201C;emotion,&#x201D;
&#x201C;feeling,&#x201D; &#x201C;desire,&#x201D; etc.), the hierarchy involved is of a different kind and
requires an entirely different type of measurement. It is a type applicable
only to the psychological process of evaluation, and may be designated as
&#x201C;<em>teleological measurement</em>.&#x201D;
